<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
    Direct distribution (not App Store) — no sandbox.

    The App Store requires sandboxing, which blocks CGEvent.tapCreate
    (Input Monitoring) and AXUIElement cross-process calls. We ship as
    a notarized DMG instead.

    Notes for future maintainers:

    • The "temporary-exception" entitlements (mach-lookup, apple-events)
      are Sandbox-only. With app-sandbox=false they are no-ops, so we
      removed them rather than carrying noise through notarization
      review.

    • Unsandboxed apps with Hardened Runtime can call CGEvent.tapCreate
      and AXUIElementCopyAttributeValue WITHOUT any extra entitlement.
      The user's Privacy & Security grant is what authorises the call,
      not an entitlement.

    • Notarization will succeed with this minimal config as long as
      Hardened Runtime is enabled in the build settings. Apple's
      notarization service does not require an explicit declaration
      for Input Monitoring or Accessibility usage — those are gated
      at runtime by TCC, not at notarization.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <false/>
</dict>
</plist>
